The paper discusses the use of algorithms and techniques to analyze and map scientific publications, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL). The focus is on identifying research topics and trends, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). The use of co-word occurrence analysis and graph layout techniques suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the analysis of the complete set of papers published in PNAS suggests a focus on computational biology (cs.CY).
